    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. Some people argue that if the goal was just to stop the massacre, then it was a win, but others say the whole thing was a massive strategic blunder because it destabilized the whole region. Do you think the 'humanitarian' justification is actually a valid way to measure success in geopolitics, or is it just a way to mask bad strategic planning?",
